crcl.base

Class PoseToleranceType

  • java.lang.Object
    • crcl.base.DataThingType
      • crcl.base.PoseToleranceType

  • public class PoseToleranceType
extends DataThingType
    PoseToleranceType is derived from DataThingType. An instance of PoseToleranceType has the following elements: Name (inherited, optional) XPointTolerance (optional) YPointTolerance (optional) ZPointTolerance (optional) XAxisTolerance (optional) ZAxisTolerance (optional). The XPointTolerance is the distance along the XAxis in current length units within which the controlled point must come from the X value of the point given in the pose with which the pose tolerance is associated. The YPointTolerance and ZPointTolerance are similar. The XAxisTolerance is the angle in current angle units within which the XAxis must come from the given XAxis. The ZAxisTolerance is similar. All five tolerances must be satisfied at the same instant.

         <element name="ZPointTolerance" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}double" minOccurs="0"/>
